	<li class="cat-item cat-item-365"><a href="http://www.gallop.net/blog/selenium-testing/" title="Selenium is emerging as one of the most robust web application testing frameworks. Selenium’s open source licensing and its support for multiple browsers, languages, and platforms make it the core engine for various browser automation tools. Selenium, and Selenium 2 (better known as WebDriver), are advanced test automation tools designed for effectively performing">Selenium Testing</a>
</li>
	<li class="cat-item cat-item-306"><a href="http://www.gallop.net/blog/service-virtualization/" title="Service Virtualization is service in which emulation of real time world is done such that developers and testers have all components available, so they can actually test the app in emulated environment, which is almost like deployed environment.Due to the emulated environment created, Service Virtualization enables product testers as well as QA teams to test an actual application in a simulated environment that is an actual replica of the deployment environment.">Service Virtualization</a>
</li>
	<li class="cat-item cat-item-170"><a href="http://www.gallop.net/blog/software-testing/" >Software Testing</a>
